Package com.twl.xg.service

Class AbstractAccessSensorService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twl.xg.service.AbstractAccessSensorService
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccessSensorService, MockAccessSensorService

    public abstract class AbstractAccessSensorService
extends java.lang.Object
    This abstract class defines the basic operations to communicate with sensors. Also provides some common methods for storing sensor or data into database. To use this class, one need to extend this abstract class first, and implement getDataFromSensor() method.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Xiaozheng Guo
    See Also:
    AccessSensorService, MockAccessSensorService

      • getDataFromSensor

        public abstract SensorDataEntity getDataFromSensor​(java.lang.String sensorIp)
                                            throws com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException
        For the input sensor IP, get current data from the sensor, map the data to a SensorDataEntity object. For the data types, use the global dataTypeList bean to decide what kind of data to fetch.
        Parameters:
        sensorIp - The IPv6 address of the sensor you want to fetch from.
        Returns:
        A SensorDataEntity object contains the data.
        Throws:
        com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException
